article.headline: Montana eases past Montana Tech 86-44
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Jordan Gregory made 5 of 6 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 24 points to lead Montana to an 86-44 victory over Montana Tech on Tuesday night. Martin Breunig added 14 points and eight rebounds, and Fabijan Krslovic finished with 13 points and nine rebounds for Grizzlies (7-8). Gregory made 9 of his 14 field goal attempts. Montana dominated in almost every facet, shooting 53.3 percent from the field and 11 of 19 from 3-point range while holding Montana Tech to 29.4 percent from the field and 6 of 20 from beyond the arc. The Grizzlies also forced 17 turnovers by the Orediggers and won the rebounding battle 39-28. Montana closed the first half on a 20-2 run to take a 41-23 lead at the half. Reid Baerlocher came off the bench to lead Montana Tech with 10 points. Adam Greger added seven points and six rebounds.
